      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "1270639316334415986",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2024-08-07T16:07:00.351+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "strong card but its applications are very narrow. This has to slot into an existing deck that is able to use 3+ dead on cards a turn. What can make ricochet worthwhile is that it scales with strength, bruise and smoking barrel's vigor more effectively then most cards. This makes it a strong card going into acts 3 and 4 where you can use it to damage cap the heart and take out elites like giant head and nemesis. The issue this card has is being overkill since you can't take it early or even mid game. You will have damage already by the time this card can be useful.",
      "author": {
